<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-24T07:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-24T07:44:00-05:00" n="701" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">853i.79682/1: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-24T12:00:00-00:44">December 24, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December
                                    24—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>91. President Barclay approved today contract between Liberian
                                Government and Pan-American Airways to start operation of air mail
                                services within a year from Liberia to Portuguese Guinea connecting
                                with other air mail services to Europe, United States and other
                                countries. Company has been granted limited monopoly as against
                                other American companies for a term of 10 years.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>